      "question": "An economy is operating below its long-run potential output. The central bank keeps interest rates constant while the government implements a large deficit-financed spending increase. A critic argues that the policy will cause 'crowding out' and fail to raise real GDP. Which combination of circumstances would most undermine the critic's argument and make the fiscal expansion most effective?",
