      "question": "Policymakers in two countries, Aldoria and Brentavia, each want to achieve higher long-run economic growth. Aldoria enacts large tax cuts for current consumption spending, while Brentavia reduces taxes specifically on business investment and funds new public infrastructure with the savings from other spending cuts. Which of the following best explains why Brentavia's policy is more likely to raise the long-run aggregate supply (LRAS)?",
