      "question": "Country X is experiencing high inflation relative to its major trading partners. Simultaneously, its central bank raises the nominal interest rate by more than the current inflation rate, ensuring that the real interest rate rises significantly. Considering both the purchasing power parity (PPP) effect and the international capital flow effect on the foreign exchange market, what is the most likely net impact on Country X's currency in the short run?",
